What I Learned

In this assignment, I learned how to build APIs using FastAPI, create routes, connect a database using SQLAlchemy, and structure a Python project properly.

Testing Experience

I learned the importance of unit tests, integration tests, and end-to-end tests. Testing helped me verify that each part of the application worked correctly.

CI/CD Experience

I learned how GitHub Actions can automatically run tests and build Docker images whenever code is pushed to GitHub.

Challenges I Faced

I faced issues with server startup, validation errors, login errors, Docker Hub authentication, and workflow failures.

How I Solved Them

I solved the issues by debugging step by step, fixing code errors, correcting secrets, updating workflows, and re-running tests.

Final Outcome

This assignment helped me understand real-world backend development, testing, deployment, and DevOps basics.
